criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Caucasian male and female patients(including Hispanic white) greater than or equal to
             40 years of age;

          -  Patients initiating coumadin therapy without a documented history of stabilized dose
             of coumadin therapy;

          -  Target INR of 2 to 3.5;

          -  Women of childbearing potential must use an effective method of birth control(e.g.
             condom,oral contraceptives, indwelling intrauterine device, abstinence.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Age less than 40 years;

          -  Patients of known Native American, Asian, or African descent;

          -  Patients with thrombocytopenia(platelet count<50x10 cells/ml);

          -  Patient has previously received coumadin and information on dosing of the patient is
             known at time of restarting coumadin;

          -  Patients with severe to moderate hepatic insufficiency (AST or ALT less than 2x the
             upper limit of normal;

          -  Clinical contraindication for coumadin therapy;

          -  Female patients with a positive pregnancy test or women who are breastfeeding
